value.value: A change in the morphology or behavior of a fibroblast resulting from exposure to an activating factor such as a cellular or soluble ligand.
Binding to L-tyrosine, 2-amino-3-(4-hydroxyphenyl)propanoic acid.

A developmental process, independent of morphogenetic (shape) change, that is required for a type B pancreatic cell to attain its fully functional state. A type B pancreatic cell is a cell located towards center of the islets of Langerhans that secretes insulin.

definition.value: These processes continue to 60 DPA in Gossypium spp.

label.value: epithelial cell proliferation involved in liver morphogenesis

value.value: The multiplication or reproduction of epithelial cells, resulting in the expansion of a cell population that contributes to the shaping of the liver.
The process in which the anatomical structures of the liver are generated and organized.
Any apoptotic process in an endothelial cell. An endothelial cell comprises the outermost layer or lining of anatomical structures and can be squamous or cuboidal.
The chemical reactions and pathways involving diatomic oxygen (O2).

label.value: establishment of protein localization to organelle

value.value: The directed movement of a protein to a specific location on or in an organelle. Encompasses establishment of localization in the membrane or lumen of a membrane-bounded organelle.

label.value: maintenance of protein localization in organelle

value.value: Any process in which a protein is maintained in a specific location a specific location on or in an organelle, and is prevented from moving elsewhere. Encompasses establishment of localization in the membrane or lumen of a membrane-bounded organelle.
A process in which a protein is transported to, or maintained in, a specific location in a membrane.
A process in which a protein is transported to, or maintained in, a specific location in the plasma membrane.
A process in which a protein is transported to, or maintained at, a location in a vacuole.

label.value: establishment of protein localization to vacuole

value.value: The directed movement of a protein to a specific location in a vacuole.

label.value: maintenance of protein location in vacuole

value.value: Any process in which a protein is maintained in a specific location in a vacuole, and is prevented from moving elsewhere.

The process in which a relatively unspecialized monocyte acquires the specialized features of a multinuclear osteoclast. An osteoclast is a specialized phagocytic cell associated with the absorption and removal of the mineralized matrix of bone tissue.
The movement of a lymphocyte within or between different tissues and organs of the body.
The movement of a T cell within or between different tissues and organs of the body.
A process in which a protein is transported to, or maintained in, the cell cortex.
A cellular protein localization process in which a protein is transported to, or maintained at, a location within the microtubule cytoskeleton.
Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a phenylalanine stimulus.

Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways within a cell or an organism involving those compounds formed as a part of the normal anabolic and catabolic processes. These processes take place in most, if not all, cells of the organism.

Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of a response to stress. Response to stress is a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a disturbance in organismal or cellular homeostasis, usually, but not necessarily, exogenous (e.g. temperature, humidity, ionizing radiation).

definition.value: Note that this term is in the subset of terms that should not be used for direct gene product annotation. Instead, select a child term or, if no appropriate child term exists, please request a new term. Direct annotations to this term may be amended during annotation QC.

value.value: A homeostatic process involved in the maintenance of a steady state level of amino acids within a cell.

Any process that modulates the rate, frequency or extent of fertilization. Fertilization is the union of gametes of opposite sexes during the process of sexual reproduction to form a zygote. It involves the fusion of the gametic nuclei (karyogamy) and cytoplasm (plasmogamy).
A process that is carried out at the cellular level which results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of a lytic vacuole.
The aggregation, arrangement and bonding together of the extracellular matrix.
An action potential that occurs in a cardiac muscle cell.
An action potential that occurs in a sinoatrial node cardiac muscle cell.
An action potential that occurs in an atrioventricular node cardiac muscle cell.
An action potential that occurs in a Purkinje myocyte.

label.value: SA node cell to atrial cardiac muscle cell signaling

value.value: Any process that mediates the transfer of information from an SA node cardiomyocyte to an atrial cardiomyocyte.

label.value: cell-cell signaling involved in cardiac conduction

value.value: Any process that mediates the transfer of information from one cell to another and contributes to the heart process that regulates cardiac muscle contraction; beginning with the generation of an action potential in the sinoatrial node and ending with regulation of contraction of the myocardium.

label.value: AV node cell to bundle of His cell signaling

value.value: Any process that mediates the transfer of information from an AV node cardiac muscle cell to a bundle of His cardiomyocyte.

label.value: Purkinje myocyte to ventricular cardiac muscle cell signaling

value.value: Any process that mediates the transfer of information from a Purkinje myocyte to a ventricular cardiac muscle cell.

label.value: cell communication involved in cardiac conduction

value.value: Any process that mediates interactions between a cell and its surroundings that contributes to the process of cardiac conduction. Encompasses interactions such as signaling or attachment between one cell and another cell, between a cell and an extracellular matrix, or between a cell and any other aspect of its environment.

label.value: AV node cell to bundle of His cell communication

value.value: The process that mediates interactions between an AV node cell and its surroundings that contributes to the process of the AV node cell communicating with a bundle of His cell in cardiac conduction. Encompasses interactions such as signaling or attachment between one cell and another cell, between a cell and an extracellular matrix, or between a cell and any other aspect of its environment.

label.value: Purkinje myocyte to ventricular cardiac muscle cell communication

value.value: The process that mediates interactions between a Purkinje myocyte and its surroundings that contributes to the process of the Purkinje myocyte communicating with a ventricular cardiac muscle cell in cardiac conduction. Encompasses interactions such as signaling or attachment between one cell and another cell, between a cell and an extracellular matrix, or between a cell and any other aspect of its environment.

label.value: SA node cell to atrial cardiac muscle cell communication

value.value: The process that mediates interactions between an SA node cardiomyocyte and its surroundings that contributes to the process of the SA node cardiomyocyte communicating with an atrial cardiomyocyte in cardiac conduction. Encompasses interactions such as signaling or attachment between one cell and another cell, between a cell and an extracellular matrix, or between a cell and any other aspect of its environment.

label.value: G protein-coupled acetylcholine receptor signaling pathway involved in heart process

value.value: A G protein-coupled acetylcholine receptor signaling pathway, which contributes to a circulatory system process carried out by the heart.

label.value: G protein-coupled receptor signaling pathway involved in heart process

value.value: An G protein-coupled receptor signaling pathway which contributes to a circulatory system process carried out by the heart.
The directed movement of L-glutamate out of the vacuole, across the vacuolar membrane.

label.value: amino acid import across plasma membrane

value.value: The directed movement of an amino acid from outside of a cell, across the plasma membrane and into the cytosol.
Any process that modulates the frequency, rate, or extent of monocyte chemotaxis.
Any process that increases the frequency, rate, or extent of monocyte chemotaxis.
Any process that decreases the frequency, rate, or extent of monocyte chemotaxis.

Any process that increases the rate, frequency or extent of microtubule nucleation. Microtubule nucleation is the 'de novo' formation of a microtubule, in which tubulin heterodimers form metastable oligomeric aggregates, some of which go on to support formation of a complete microtubule. Microtubule nucleation usually occurs from a specific site within a cell.

label.value: positive regulation of cell cycle process

value.value: Any process that increases the rate, frequency or extent of a cellular process that is involved in the progression of biochemical and morphological phases and events that occur in a cell during successive cell replication or nuclear replication events.

Any process that modulates the rate, frequency or extent of ribosome biogenesis. Ribosome biogenesis is the cellular process that results in the biosynthesis of constituent macromolecules, assembly, and arrangement of constituent parts of ribosome subunits.

Any process that increases the rate, frequency or extent of ribosome biogenesis. Ribosome biogenesis is the cellular process that results in the biosynthesis of constituent macromolecules, assembly, and arrangement of constituent parts of ribosome subunits.

Any process that decreases the rate, frequency or extent of ribosome biogenesis. Ribosome biogenesis is the cellular process that results in the biosynthesis of constituent macromolecules, assembly, and arrangement of constituent parts of ribosome subunits.
